Exxon Mobil stock price target cut to $83 from $86 at CFRA

Jul. 28, 2017 at 1:28 p.m. ET
by Tomi Kilgore









Chevron swings to profit as charges shrink
Chevron Corp. swung to a profit in the second quarter as it benefited from higher crude oil and natural gas prices and efforts to cut costs throughout its operations. Chevron's average sales price per barrel of crude oil and natural gas liquids was $41, up from $36 in the year-ago period. The company's average price of natural gas was $2.32 per thousand cubic feet, nearly double the price it realized a year ago.

